caption: Best place is Mount Pleasant.
Good experience

I go to Dos Gringos as a treat to myself on my days off from work! They are very covid safe, so don't let that stop you from going. I usually get coffee and a pastry but today got the lentil breakfast burritto and will definitely be ordering it again! It is SO DELICIOUS! Very flavorful and filling. I feel lucky to have this place in my neighborhood!
Large portions, great price, friendly staff, and lots of veg-friendly options. Love this neighborhood staple!

A wonderful part of the Mount Pleasant neighborhood. The food is simple, fresh, and delicious. The coffee is great, and everything is reasonably priced. The owner and her team are also unfailing, genuinely friendly. Whether stopping in for a quick coffee or an extended lunch, every trip to Dos Gringos is a pleasure!
Absolutely love it. A neighborhood staple. Nothing else like it!
Breakfast with Generous portions of yummy ingredients done just the way you want it

Dos gringos is funky, friendly, tasty, and affordable. The Plato Típico is a great meal deal. Eating here, or stopping by for a cup of coffee or a bagel sandwich just feels like tapping into the heart Mt. Pleasant — always worth it.

I love this place. The food is great and you can get it for an excellent price. I was so impressed by the quality given how low the prices were. I would definitely recommend going here if you need a quick bite or a coffee.
So happy this place still exists They are the best example of a family restaurant that is truly homey!
A staple!
Great food and service!
A great place for brunch!  I loved it!
Friendly.warm
Coffee and food delicious
I love every special I’ve ever had here. Great people great food part of a great street
This is one of my favorite places in the NW. lovely atmosphere, excellent prices, great food. Perfect for a brunch morning during the weekend.

This was literally the worst place I have ever been to. There were so many ROACHES!! Crawling everywhere on the register, the machine that prints out the receipts, the pastries, the table with the condiments, the water cups, we even found a BABY ROACH in our Drink. The food was horrible, it’s smelled and tasted old. The bagels are stale. We didn’t even eat our food we just left. We tried it again just to give it another chance, and I watched he drop someone’s food pick it up and send it out. Worst experience ever. Would definitely not recommend to anyone

I love this place and everything about it. Great food (made with love), amazing coffee, chill space! Alice has really created one of Mt. Pleasant's greatest neighborhood sanctuaries. It's local businesses like this that make a neighborhood a community. Thanks to the entire, beautiful crew there!
Made to order breakfast for my Keto diet.  Simply good and a neighborhood must visit.
Nice neighborhood spot. Food was pretty good for an affordable price. I like the restaurants character too.
Awesome local spot for lunch.

Owner is friendly enough, but unfortunately the menu is not. An odd, eclectic pseudo-Mexican without much seasoning, frozen bagged vegetables, and a strange overuse of eggs. I wanted to like it, but I didn't. Desperately needs a spice rack and some fresher produce.
Dos Gringos is a neighborhood casual place.  lt has ice cream in the basement, vegan and non vegan options. Intercambio days.
I love this neighborhood spot. Really unpretentious place to read a book and have a bite to eat. I particularly enjoy their frittata del dia.

I always feel welcome at this mainstay on Mount Pleasant Street. Simple, wholesome food paired with a wide variety of beverages makes Dos Gringos an excellent choice to fill any belly. Very reasonably priced, and always delicious.

Super low-key, great catch-up coffee shop. Don't come if you're rushed, that's not the point of this place. It's perfect to sit with a friend, wait a bit depending on the line, and then enjoy the balcony or the patio.  Another plus: their prices are quite good given their location.  Their warm food has yet to disappoint - that I have anything against the pastries - they're just better known for using their kitchen :)
Cozy restaurant/cafe in Mt. Pleasant with great prices.
The food won't blow your away but you'll enjoy the comfortable atmosphere and friendly staff

The service here was horrible. The cashier must have been hung over or high. He didn't understand my question and looked genuinely upset that i was asking him anything at all. The food was great though.
One of my favorite server spots in DC. Get the primo avocado! You won’t be disappointed!
A wonderful place to relax and drink excellent coffee.
(Translated by Google) Excellent  (Original) Excelente
Lovely people, a true cornerstone of the community
Every time I've visited Dos Gringos, I've had great food and a great experience. The coffee in particular was great!

This place is a staple of the community and prides itself on being a reflection of it. The sandwiches are amazing (anything with avocado) and the cozy atmosphere will make you want to stick around for a while. Love their baked goods, too - dessert is a must!
Staff was very friendly and helpful. I got the special, and a blueberry Italian soda. Both were excellent.
Best avocado sandwich in the city!!! (Primo avocado classico) - great atmosphere, a Mount Pleasant staple.
Great food Grear service Nice area the Bario.

Funny that I had the similar experience at Dos Gringos recently; bought two sandwiches for dinner around their closing time, 7.45pm and got chicken curry salad, The bread was was very hard and the chicken curry salad tasted horrible. we could not eat after the first bite.   Sad to see this little joint losing its quality food:(

I loved this place but recently got four sets of sandwiches (spring chicken salad w avocado and chicken curry salad) in two occasions for guest and our dinner - sadly both times  it had a strong, strange smell and taste really bad - we had to throw away all those sandwiches! Today I had to buy again and told Alex about past experience but still did not taste good - tasted stale. Overall quality has dropped.
Excellent breakfast
Poor cold coffee
Its a great place with great food. Customer service is grand. Food is quickly prepared to your liking.
Good was not good and it was expensive. It's a very small place with old used furniture.

(Translated by Google) Excellent food and sublime service are bilingual and everything they prepare is completely nutritious and homemade, I highly recommend it !!  (Original) Excelente comida y el servicio sublime son bilingües y es completamente nutritivo y casero todo lo que preparan,lo recomiendo ampliamente!!
Would be 5 if they accepted mobile payment
Great cozy and authentic place.

Wonderful place to get a simple coffee or food. No pretention there, no fancy decoration. But the ambiance is very cosy, the employees super nice and their food is delicious with an extensive choice of veggies. Also a very affordable place. I will go back!
Great for a very filling meal
lovely people, wonderful food.. just the right mix of cute and down-to-earth, especially among DC’s many trendy/bougie spots
Amazing little neighborhood gem. Feels like a good friend's living room. A bit in the pricy side...
You know what you're getting into
A small cozy space with healthy and refreshing food. Will definitely be back.

I had the most delicious tortilla pie here - it was the daily special. It tasted like the best dinner my mom ever made for me. The owner was so warm and inviting. The restaurant has plenty of outdoor seating on two porch levels. I can't wait to come back here!

Bad coffee (tasting like it was brewed last night), inedible food. The potatoes were clearly old/ leftover dried out and mealy. The plantains I had to spit out (first time ever doing that in public place). They were perhaps not ripe? They were unyielding, dry, and also mealy. Shudder. Not worth paying for.
Food was incredible! Fresh, simple and healthy. The menu is adequate, great brunch, you won't regret it. Not about atmosphere, it's about the food. Nice folks also.
Tasty healthy food, nice atmosphere, very good prices.
Reasonably priced neighborhood joint with good breakfast that focuses (but not exclusively) on vegetarian/vegan food. Service is adequate though sometimes harried.

Alex the Owner is such a Wonder Woman! An incredible person. A hardworker and the business reflects just that. A great place tp eat and drink your coffee/tea any time of the day. Stop giving your money to Starbucks and support local business owners.
Yum

This is a great, genuine DC neighborhood cafe. It's home cooked (by mom the hippie) food in a simple but comfortable space. If you want a good meal in a community setting this is the place for you. Note, the silverware won't match, so if this makes you nervous, maybe not the place for you.
Great affordable Mexican cuisine with plenty of vegetarian options!
Good food, good coffee, good people!
Great coffee!
This is a favorite Mt. Pleasant spot. Locals frequent this bilingual, homey cafe with its' view of Mt. Pleasant Street and amazing salmon bagel (with tomato, capers, cream cheese).
Best local cafe .
best breakfast in dc. get a frittata!
Excellent food, great service

On a sunny day, breakfast sandwiches here are a real treat. (Inside is nothing special, but they have outdoor seating.) Food selection is larger than average - expect to spend some time choosing! Excellent value for money.
Cheap,  simple,  and tasty.  Friendly home like feeling too.
This is a quant, cozy place. The owner is very patient, polite and has a good sense of humor. This was my first time there and I'm surely going to return.
Awesome options! Try a bagger! You never know what you're gonna get, but it's always good! Their ice cream is also top notch.
Bad coffee.  Worse food (it's mostly microwaved).  Also seems they were recently subject to health code violations.
The best waffles of dc

I stopped by here for take out. The black bean burrito had a sour taste, the rice was not cooked and it was greasy. I saw them stick it in the microwave before handing it to me. I think all they did was throw some stuff in a tortilla, wrap and nuke. I can do a better job at home. It was also very stuffy in there. I  called my credit card to contest the charge and thankfully got refunded.

A nice dynamic place to sit down, have a conversation and get your belly full on a vegan or veggie sandwich etc. not too expensive either. The decor could use some touches though to get a more non-cafeteria look.
Crappy food, dirty interior, but at least it's cheap.

Pretty good food, though the staff wasn't too excited to see me. Their prices were reasonable and the menu had some pretty interesting offerings. I don't think the barista had much of a clue as to how to make a latte, but the wrap was so good that it didn't really matter.
My goto local spot in Columbia Heights / Mt. Pleasant for breakfast. I love the quirkiness of this place. The food is quite good too. If you're vegetarian or vegan, this place is made for you.
